    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p>At 11th level, you gain the ability to create an orb of light that erupts into a devastating explosion. As an action, you magically create an orb and hurl it at a point you choose within 150 feet, where it erupts into a sphere of radiant light for a brief but deadly instant.</p><p>Each creature in that 20-foot-radius sphere must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take [[/damage 2d6 type=radiant]] damage. A creature doesn't need to make the save if the creature is behind &amp;Reference[rule=totalcover]{total cover} that is opaque.</p><p>You can increase the sphere's damage by spending ki points. Each point you spend, to a maximum of 3, increases the damage by [[/damage 2d6]].</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
